{"description":"When the logger method is resolved, +with a single parameter+, but the type of this parameter is not resolved, the rule fails.\r\nIn such cases, implementations of rule RSPEC-3457 and RSPEC-2275 assume that there is necessarily two arguments, leading to an {{IndexOutOfBoundsException}}.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nclass A {\r\n  private static final org.slf4j.Logger LOG \u003d org.slf4j.LoggerFactory.getLogger(A.class);\r\n\r\n  void bar() {\r\n    unknown((a, b) -\u003e {\r\n      LOG.info(a.foo());  // method resolved thanks to inference, but not the type of the argument\r\n    });\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n{code}","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"5.1.1"}